DataElement.preferredName: Chromint Software Specified Peak Resolution java.lang.String
DataElement.preferredDefinition: A method for detection of chromatography peaks based on the analysis of the profile of the first derivative of the signal calculated with a Savitzky Golay filter. This provides a list of peaks and their position with typically around 25 peaks detected per electropherogram.:Clearly and explicitly stated.:The most extreme possible amount or value; the highest point._The size of the smallest element that can be separated from neighboring elements._Generic value domain for a java datatype that is a class that represents character strings.
